  "message": "test(fixtures): Add unencrypted pages verification fixture\n\nAdd a new test fixture for testing the pages verification logic against\nan unencrypted site deployment. This complements the existing fixtures:\n\n- valid/           - Standard encrypted valid site\n- missing_required/ - Site missing required files\n- missing_required_no_viewer/ - Missing viewer.js specifically\n- secret_leak/     - Site with exposed recovery secret\n- unencrypted/     - NEW: Site without encryption enabled\n\nThe fixture follows the established structure with .nojekyll, auth.js,\nconfig.json, index.html, payload/, robots.txt, styles.css, sw.js, and\nviewer.js. The payload contains data.db instead of encrypted chunks,\nrepresenting an unencrypted deployment scenario.\n\nThis enables testing edge cases where encryption is disabled, ensuring\nthe verification logic handles both encrypted and unencrypted sites.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
